🌟 GlowField

GlowField is a server-side Fabric mod that creates dynamic, configurable force-field zones using Respawn Anchors. These zones protect areas by preventing mob spawns, damaging hostile entities, and rendering a visible particle-based barrier—all without requiring any client-side mods.

⸻

⚡ Features

🛡️ Force Field Zones
	•	Create protected areas using 4 Respawn Anchors
	•	Forms a rectangular 3D zone from world bottom to top
	•	Fully server-side — vanilla clients can join without installing anything

⸻

🔋 Charge-Based Behavior

Zones automatically change behavior based on anchor charge levels:
	•	All anchors fully charged (4 charges)
→ Force Field Mode
	•	Damages mobs that enter
	•	Strong visual particle barrier
	•	All anchors have ≥1 charge
→ Spawn Prevention Mode
	•	Prevents hostile mob spawning
	•	Softer visual effect
	•	Any anchor uncharged
→ Inactive
	•	Zone does nothing

⸻

⚠️ Degradation System

Force fields are not infinite:
	•	Every N mobs prevented or damaged (configurable)
→ reduces anchor charge by 1
	•	Encourages maintenance and recharging

⸻

✨ Particle Force Field
	•	Full 3D perimeter rendering
	•	Configurable particle types per state:
	•	Force Field → e.g. portal
	•	Spawn Prevention → e.g. smoke
	•	Inactive → e.g. end rod
	•	Rendered server-side via packets

⸻

🧠 Smart Performance Design
	•	Chunk-indexed zones (no global scanning)
	•	Event-driven updates (no ticking loops)
	•	Efficient entity queries via bounding boxes
	•	Scales to many zones without lag

⸻

💾 Persistent Zones
	•	Zones are saved to disk (NBT)
	•	Automatically restored on server restart
	•	Includes:
	•	Anchor positions
	•	Owner
	•	Zone name

⸻

👤 Ownership & Naming
	•	Zones track the player who created them
		•	(Optional) Support for naming via Name Tags

    ⸻

    📦 Installation

    Requirements
    	•	Minecraft 1.21.x (Fabric)
    	•	Fabric Loader 0.16+
    	•	Fabric API

    Steps
    	1.	Install Fabric Loader
    	2.	Install Fabric API
    	3.	Drop the GlowField .jar into your /mods folder
    	4.	Start the server

    ⸻

    ⚙️ Configuration

    Config file is generated at: /config/glowfield.json

    Options
    	•	enableParticles — toggle rendering
    	•	suppressionThreshold — mobs required to degrade field
    	•	forceFieldDamage — damage dealt to mobs
    	•	forceFieldParticle — particle for full field
    	•	spawnPreventionParticle — particle for weak field
    	•	inactiveParticle — fallback particle

    ⸻

    🧱 How to Use
    	1.	Place 4 Respawn Anchors in a rectangle (corners)
    	2.	Charge them using Glowstone
    	3.	Ensure all anchors meet charge requirements
    	4.	Zone activates automatically